Type: Package
Package: climateAPI
Title: Weather Data Analysis
Version: 0.1.0
Author: person("Mateo","Pesa",
    email="msp256@cornell.edu",role=c("aut","cre"))
Maintainer: Mateo Pesa <msp256@cornell.edu>
Description: climateAPI is a package designed to analyze data from the US
    Climate Reference Network (USCRN), which is a set of high quality
    weather stations maintained by the National Centers for Environmental
    Information (NCEI) within the National Oceanic and Atmospheric
    Administration (NOAA).  It primarily focuses on analyzing stations
    around America, interpolating data from these stations to account for
    the entire contiguous USA, and looking at yearly patterns and data for
    all of America.
